Once again, it has become necessary to assure Nigerians that despite the huge burden of under-recovery, the Federal Government is not in a hurry to increase the price of Premium Motor Spirit (petrol) to reflect current market realities.According to the press statement endorsed by H. G. Timipre Sylva, Hon. Minister of State for Petroleum at Abuja and sent through the media team of NNPC saying Thecurrent price of petrol will be retained in the month of June until the ongoing engagement with organized labour is concluded. The statement further disclosed that This clarification becomes necessary in the light of recent reports regarding the resolution of the Nigeria Governors Forum to increase the pump price of petrol. In this regard, I would like to strongly urge petroleum products marketers not to engage in any activity that could jeopardize the seamless supply and distribution system in place, he added “I also urge members of the public to avoid panic buying because the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) has enough stock of petroleum products to keep the nation wet.”